		<h3><div id="11">ADDITIONAL TERMS</div></h3>
		<p><h4>Termination Rights; Discontinuation of Courses and Content.</h4>You agree that GetEducated, in its sole discretion, may terminate your use of the GetEducated Site or your participation in it, for any reason or no reason, upon notice to you. It is GetEducated's policy to terminate in appropriate circumstances the accounts of users of the GetEducated Site who are repeat copyright infringers. GetEducated and the GetEducated Participants reserve the right at any time in their sole discretion to cancel, delay, reschedule or alter the format of any course offered through GetEducated, or to cease providing any part or all of the GetEducated Site content or related services, and you agree that neither GetEducated nor any of the GetEducated Participants will have any liability to you for such an action. If you no longer desire to participate in the GetEducated Site, you may terminate your participation at any time. The rights granted to you hereunder will terminate upon any termination of your right to use the GetEducated Site, but the other provisions of the Agreements will survive any such termination.</p>
		<p><h4>Entire Agreement.</h4>The Agreements constitute the entire agreement between you and GetEducated with respect to your use of the GetEducated Site, superseding any prior agreements between you and GetEducated regarding your use of the GetEducated Site.</p>
		<p><h4>Waiver and Severability.</h4>The failure of GetEducated to exercise or enforce any right or provision of the Agreements shall not constitute a waiver of such right or provision. If any provision of the Agreements is found by a court of competent jurisdiction to be invalid, the parties nevertheless agree that the court should endeavor to give effect to the parties' intentions as reflected in the provision and the other provisions of the Agreements shall remain in full force and effect.</p>
		<p><h4>Choice of Law/Forum Selection.</h4>You agree that the Agreements and any claim or dispute arising out of or relating to the Agreements or any content or service obtained from or through the GetEducated Site will be governed by the laws of the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, excluding its conflicts of law provisions. You agree that all such claims and disputes will be heard and resolved exclusively in the federal or state courts located in and serving Cambridge, Massachusetts, U.S.A. You consent to the personal jurisdiction of those courts over you for this purpose, and you waive and agree not to assert any objection to such proceedings in those courts (including any defense or objection of lack of proper jurisdiction or venue or inconvenience of forum).</p>
